        "text": "I’m honestly sick and tired of going down to the leasing office at BLVD Loudoun Station Gramercy East just for absolutely nothing to get resolved. We were promised a $500 referral credit for referring someone who moved in before March 31st. The people we referred moved in on March 17th, and we even went on TWO tours with them ourselves. Since then, we’ve been to the leasing office more than 5 times about this exact issue and still nothing has been done. It is now May 10th. At this point it feels like residents just get ignored and given the runaround.\n\nAnother thing — people in this apartment complex are unbelievably sensitive about noise. You flush the toilet or walk around your apartment and the next morning you get an email from the leasing office about “late night noise.” It’s honestly ridiculous. We understand apartment living comes with noise because we ARE sharing a building with other people. Some residents act like they expect complete silence 24/7, and the leasing office seems to entertain every minor complaint instead of being realistic about apartment living.\n\nI take back my good review from a few months ago since i was being nice but we pay too much for people to be acting like this is elementary school or something. I can now understand why Karen’s become Karen’s….",
